Write the setControlPointWeight method in the NurbsCurve3D class.
Remember to respond with a snippet in the form of the following:
```
class NurbsCurve3D {
    setControlPointWeight(index, weight) {
        // your code here
    }
}
```

```javascript
class NurbsCurve3D {
    setControlPointWeight(index, weight) {
         if (index < 0 || index >= this.weights.length) {
            console.error('Control point index out of bounds.');
            return;
        }
        if(typeof weight !== 'number'){
             console.error('Weight must be a number.');
             return;
        }
        this.weights[index] = weight;
    }
}
```
